    <!-- Hotspot descriptions -->
    <string name="hotspot_desc_starbucks">Riverside Starbucks in Tamsui, with glass-window views, ~2.0 km from the tower (WNW, ~283°). **The best chance to catch the sun through the tower is around the summer solstice.** A relaxed vantage point — the comfiest fallback when perfect alignment isn\'t in season.</string>
    <string name="hotspot_desc_customs_wharf">The historic Customs Wharf, ~1.4 km from the tower (due west, ~274°). **Two alignment windows a year: early April and mid-September** (the sun passes 274° just after the spring equinox / before the autumn equinox). Heritage brick walls plus the bridge sunset make for a rich, historical composition.</string>
    <string name="hotspot_desc_mackay_landing">Mackay Landing, ~2.0 km from the tower (WNW, ~283°). Like the other Tamsui-bank spots, its high-azimuth alignment window is **around the summer solstice (late May, late July).**</string>
    <string name="hotspot_desc_tamsui_ferry">Tamsui Old Street pier, ~2.2 km from the tower (WNW, ~286°). **Two windows, late May and late July** (near the summer-solstice high azimuth).</string>
    <string name="hotspot_desc_riverside_park_2">Riverside Park 2, ~2.5 km from the tower (WNW, ~287°). High-azimuth alignment window **around the summer solstice.**</string>
    <string name="hotspot_desc_riverside_park_1">Riverside Park 1, ~2.7 km from the tower (WNW, ~288°). Best chance to catch the sun through the tower when the sun nears this bearing **around the summer solstice.**</string>
    <string name="hotspot_desc_tamsui_mrt">Riverside by Tamsui MRT station, ~2.9 km from the tower (WNW, ~288°). Closest **around the summer solstice**; easy to reach, good for a spur-of-the-moment trip.</string>
    <string name="hotspot_desc_bali">Bali Left Bank Park, ~1.9 km from the tower (NW, ~323°), 25° beyond the sun\'s azimuth range. Closest **around the summer solstice** when the sun reaches 298°; a wide lens can frame the tower and sunset together.</string>
    <string name="hotspot_desc_bali_ferry">Bali Ferry Pier, ~2.1 km from the tower (NW, ~317°), 19° beyond the sun\'s azimuth range. Closest **around the summer solstice.** The Tamsui Old Street skyline across the river can enter the frame.</string>

